# Normalize line endings across platforms.
#
# JDesk's codegen emits LF and several tests compare generated output byte-for-byte
# against committed fixtures (the codegen golden files and the public-API baseline).
# Without this file, a Windows checkout under `core.autocrlf=true` rewrites those LF
# fixtures to CRLF in the working tree and `./gradlew check` fails with spurious
# line-ending diffs. Forcing LF in the working tree on every OS keeps the fixtures
# identical to what CI (Linux/macOS) produces.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows batch scripts must stay CRLF to run correctly.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf

# Binary assets — never apply line-ending or text conversion.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.icns binary
*.webp binary
*.pdf binary
*.jar binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
*.tar binary
*.dll binary
*.dylib binary
*.so binary
*.lib binary
*.keystore binary
*.jks binary
*.p12 binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
